item.title: Israel again orders residents to evacuate areas of Gaza City it once said were cleared of Hamas
item.description: The Israeli military ordered Palestinians to evacuate Gaza City and head south as it expanded operations in the north of the enclave, an area it previously said it had cleared of Hamas fighters.

item.title: Maryland woman scores big prize trying lottery game for the first time
item.description: A Maryland woman decided to try something new during a night out with friends and won $31,233 from the Maryland Lottery's Racetrax virtual horse racing game.

item.title: Man sentenced to 4-plus years in death of original ‘Mickey Mouse Club’ cast member
item.description: A man charged in the death of Dennis Day, an original cast member on Walt Disney’s “Mickey Mouse Club” television program in the 1950s, has been sentenced to just over four years in prison after entering a modified guilty plea this week.

item.title: Video shows Uruguayan soccer stars brawl with Colombia fans at Copa America semifinal
item.description: The second Copa America semifinal took a violent turn when Uruguayan players brawled with fans in the stands following their elimination at the hands of Colombia. Cameras captured several players walking into the stands at the Bank of America Stadium in Charlotte, North Carolina, and exchanging punches with Colombia fans as security staff tried to hold the players back.
